                <li class="by">January 10, 2009 at 11:52 am</li>
                <li class="by"><a href="https://www.inspire.com/groups/stop-sarcoidosis/discussion/the-spoon-theory-read-this-youll-be-glad-you-did/reply/246912/flag/">Report post</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <p>My partner started remicade for skin sarc in November and it has worked wonders on the lesions; they&#39;re basically gone except for the discolorations.  It does leave him VERY tired, especially from 3-8 days (plus or minus a day or two) after the infusion.<br />
<br />
He finally got to see someone at the Sarc Clinic at Johns Hopkins and between that doc and the dermatologist he has, we think he can be justifiably put on 8-week regimen of remicade infusions for a year.  Now I don&#39;t know how effective remicade is on other forms of sarc like yours.  Please let us know how you are doing with this treatment, though.</p>
        <div class="clear"></div>
    </div>
