        <p>I am so proud of you for how you handled that.  My pain has turned me into such a nasty BITCH.  I would have sworn like a sailor thrown things at her and never spoke to her again.<br />
<br />
I am angry all the time and although I no longer feel sorry for myself I am bitter at the people who do feel well. I am surrounded by people who constantly chastise me for not feeling well. <br />
<br />
I have heard time and time again how I keep surrounding myself with people who are just like me (mental) and we all enable each other to feel this way.<br />
<br />
What did you draw from to be Proactive rather than Reactive ?  How do you find the patience to keep explaining your illness to those who should know it better than you.</p>
